09/04/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The European Commission's vice-president in charge of administration, auditing and anti-fraud, Siim Kallas, hailed Romania on Friday (7 April) for the progress achieved in combating fraud but called for more transparency in public acquisitions, decision-making and management of community funds.
Kallas was in Bucharest for talks with Romanian President Traian Basescu and Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu.
(Rompres, AP - 07/04/06)
